{'book': {'publisher': 'Pearson College Div', 'synopsis': 'Designed to give users an experience of actual inclusive classrooms, this CD-ROM contains 36 video clips showing inclusion strategies in four different grade levels. An accompanying \x93activity book\x94 provides readers with a basic background for the inclusive classroom experience, and includes discussions of instructional planning, managing behavior, and collaboration. With comments by experts in special education, users learn the connections to CEC and INTASC standards. The CD-ROM includes 36 video clips that show nine inclusion strategies for each grade level: preschool, sixth grade Social Studies, middle school team meeting, and high school physics. The various clips show children with learning disabilities, attention deficit disorders, and mild/moderate disabilities being successfully engaged in the classroom and in learning by expert teachers. For educators involved in the special education departments in grammar, middle, and high school. Also an excellent resource for parents of children with mild/moderate disabilites.', 'language': 'en', 'image': 'https://images.isbndb.com/covers/62/81/9780131136281.jpg', 'title_long': 'Inclusive Classrooms: Video Cases on Cd-Rom Activity and Learning Guide', 'edition': 'First Edition', 'dimensions': 'Height: 10.5 Inches, Length: 8 Inches, Weight: 0.59083886216 Pounds, Width: 0.25 Inches', 'dimensions_structured': {'length': {'unit': 'inches', 'value': 8}, 'width': {'unit': 'inches', 'value': 0.25}, 'weight': {'unit': 'pounds', 'value': 0.59083886216}, 'height': {'unit': 'inches', 'value': 10.5}}, 'pages': 80, 'date_published': '2003', 'subjects': ['Education & Teaching', 'Schools & Teaching', 'Special Education', 'Specialty Boutique', 'New, Used & Rental Textbooks'], 'authors': ['Anne M. Bauer', 'Stephen Kroeger'], 'title': 'Inclusive Classrooms: Video Cases on Cd-Rom Activity and Learning Guide', 'isbn13': '9780131136281', 'msrp': 20, 'binding': 'Paperback', 'isb